26 10:42 AM        4027694 [31;1mattention.zip[0m\r\n-a---           3/15/2026  3:00 PM     1004974456 [31;1mcircuit_lm.zip[0m\r\n-a---            3/4/2026  1:07 AM           1249 [32;1mcreate_zip.py[0m\r\n-a---            3/3/2026 12:07 PM          26397 EXPERIMENT_RESULTS_INVENTORY.json\r\n-a---            3/3/2026 12:07 PM          10074 EXPERIMENT_RESULTS_MANIFEST.json\r\n-a---            3/3/2026 12:07 PM          16558 EXPERIMENT_RESULTS_MANIFEST.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774114344225}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e703a4c","parentId":"797ac21a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:32:28.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting! Let me look at some key files:1. COMPOUND_BREAKTHROUGH_README.md in EXP - sounds like breakthrough experiments\n2. COGNITIVE_AGENT_PLAN.md in mind - cognitive agent stuff\n3. CONTINUOUS_IMPROVEMENT_QUICK_START.md - could be relevant to improving myself\n4. The EXPERIMENT_RESULTS_MANIFEST.md in research\n5. The neu-project notebooks folder\n\nLet me read some of these key files.","thinkingSignature":"6f2d6b6dd2bf96856ba66edb3fb80e545c007dcefc33a0f7fe14b9d7f0524cc6"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me read the most promising files — the breakthrough experiments readme, cognitive agent plan, and the experiment manifest.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ftiehdv9m30e_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/EXP/experiments/COMPOUND_BREAKTHROUGH_README.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19842,"output":170,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31886,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774114344230}}
{"type":"message","id":"26168572","parentId":"5e703a4c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:32:29.030Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ftiehdv9m30e_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Compound Breakthrough Discovery System\r\n\r\n**Goal**: Discover breakthrough insights through systematic compound experimentation, data mining, and counterintuitive hypothesis testing.\r\n\r\nThis system implements three complementary approaches to finding breakthroughs:\r\n\r\n1. **Compound Experiments** - Test combinations of optimizations to find synergies\r\n2. **Insight Discovery** - Mine accumulated data for hidden patterns\r\n3. **Counterintuitive Testing** - Challenge assumptions with paradoxical hypotheses\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Quick Start\r\n\r\n### 1. Run Compound Experiments\r\n\r\nTest combinations of your production-ready experiments to find synergies:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Run all high-value combinations\r\npython experiments/compound_breakthrough_experiments.py\r\n\r\n# Run specific combination\r\npython experiments/compound_breakthrough_experiments.py --combo \"7+9+11\"\r\n\r\n# Run all combinations up to size 3\r\npython experiments/compound_breakthrough_experiments.py --all --max-size 3\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What it does:**\r\n- Runs combinations of experiments 7, 9, 11, 13, 20, 23, 24\r\n- Calculates expected compound effects (multiplicative)\r\n- Detects synergies where actual > expected\r\n- Identifies counterintuitive results\r\n- Finds threshold effects\r\n\r\n**Output:**\r\n- `results/compound_experiments/compound_results_*.json` - Detailed results\r\n- `results/compound_experiments/breakthrough_report_*.json` - Analysis report\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 2. Discover Insights from Data\r\n\r\nMine all your accumulated experiment data for hidden patterns:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Full analysis (recommended)\r\npython experiments/insight_discovery_analyzer.py --analyze-all\r\n\r\n# Just correlations\r\npython experiments/insight_discovery_analyzer.py --correlations\r\n\r\n# Just thresholds\r\npython experiments/insight_discovery_analyzer.py --thresholds\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What it discovers:**\r\n- **Correlations**: Strong relationships between variables (expected or surprising)\r\n- **Thresholds**: Points where behavior changes suddenly (breakthrough points)\r\n- **Anomalies**: Outliers that might indicate breakthroughs\r\n- **Optimal Combinations**: Best-performing configurations\r\n- **Counterintuitive Patterns**: Results that challenge assumptions\r\n\r\n**Output:**\r\n- `results/insights/insight_report_*.json` - Comprehensive insight report\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### 3. Test Counterintuitive Hypotheses\r\n\r\nChallenge conventional wisdom with paradoxical ideas:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Test all hypotheses\r\npython experiments/counterintuitive_hypotheses.py --all\r\n\r\n# Test specific hypothesis\r\npython experiments/counterintuitive_hypotheses.py --hypothesis \"more_eviction_better\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Hypotheses tested:**\r\n- `more_eviction_better` - More aggressive eviction improves performance\r\n- `smaller_batches_higher_throughput` - Smaller batches = higher throughput\r\n- `random_eviction_beats_smart` - Random eviction beats cost-model eviction\r\n- `worse_hit_rate_better_latency` - Lower hit rate improves latency\r\n- `memory_sharing_hurts` - Sharing memory hurts performance\r\n- `no_prefetch_better` - No prefetching beats predictive prefetching\r\n- `higher_latency_variance_better` - Higher variance improves throughput\r\n\r\n**Output:**\r\n- `results/counterintuitive/counterintuitive_results_*.json` - Hypothesis test results\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Understanding the Results\r\n\r\n### Compound Experiments\r\n\r\n**Synergy Detection:**\r\n- If combining Exp 7 (64% memory reduction) + Exp 9 (3x throughput) gives >3.5x throughput, that's a synergy\r\n- Look for `synergy_percent > 10%` in the report\r\n\r\n**Threshold Effects:**\r\n- When combining 2 experiments gives 2x improvement, but 3 gives 5x (not 3x), that's a threshold\r\n- These are breakthrough points where effects compound non-linearly\r\n\r\n**Counterintuitive Results:**\r\n- If Exp 7 shows memory reduction but latency gets worse, that's counterintuitive\r\n- These may reveal hidden trade-offs or new principles\r\n\r\n### Insight Discovery\r\n\r\n**High-Confidence Correlations (≥0.8):**\r\n- These reveal direct relationships you can exploit\r\n- Example: \"Memory reduction strongly correlates with batch size\" → optimize memory to increase batches\r\n\r\n**Threshold Effects:**\r\n- Points where small changes cause large effects\r\n- Example: \"At batch_size=4, throughput jumps 50%\" → this is a breakthrough point\r\n\r\n**Anomalies:**\r\n- Experiments that performed way better/worse than expected\r\n- These may indicate breakthrough configurations or reveal edge cases\r\n\r\n### Counterintuitive Hypotheses\r\n\r\n**Confirmed Hypotheses:**\r\n- If a paradoxical hypothesis is confirmed, it challenges fundamental assumptions\r\n- These are the most likely to lead to breakthroughs\r\n- Example: \"More eviction = better performance\" confirmed → new eviction strategy\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Workflow for Breakthrough Discovery\r\n\r\n### Phase 1: Baseline Analysis (Week 1)\r\n\r\n1. **Run insight discovery** on all existing data\r\n   ```bash\r\n   python experiments/insight_discovery_analyzer.py --analyze-all\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n2. **Review insights** for patterns:\r\n   - What correlations are surprising?\r\n   - Are there threshold effects?\r\n   - What anomalies stand out?\r\n\r\n3. **Document findings** in a research log\r\n\r\n### Phase 2: Compound Testing (Week 2-3)\r\n\r\n1. **Run compound experiments** on high-value combinations\r\n   ```bash\r\n   python experiments/compound_breakthrough_experiments.py --all --max-size 3\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n2. **Identify synergies:**\r\n   - Which combinations exceed expected?\r\n   - Are there threshold effects at certain sizes?\r\n\r\n3. **Deep dive** into promising combinations:\r\n   - Run more iterations\r\n   - Test at different scales\r\n   - Validate on production traces\r\n\r\n### Phase 3: Counterintuitive Exploration (Week 4)\r\n\r\n1. **Test all counterintuitive hypotheses**\r\n   ```bash\r\n   python experiments/counterintuitive_hypotheses.py --all\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n2. **For confirmed hypotheses:**\r\n   - Design real experiments (not simulations)\r\n   - Test in controlled conditions\r\n   - Measure carefully\r\n\r\n3. **Document counterintuitive findings:**\r\n   - Why did it work?\r\n   - What principle does it reveal?\r\n   - How can we exploit it?\r\n\r\n### Phase 4: Synthesis (Week 5)\r\n\r\n1. **Combine insights:**\r\n   - Do compound synergies align with discovered correlations?\r\n   - Do counterintuitive results explain anomalies?\r\n   - Are there patterns across all three approaches?\r\n\r\n2. **Formulate breakthrough hypotheses:**\r\n   - Based on all evidence, what's the breakthrough?\r\n   - Design validation experiments\r\n   - Test at scale\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Example: Finding a Breakthrough\r\n\r\n### Scenario: Discovering Memory-Latency Synergy\r\n\r\n1. **Insight Discovery** reveals:\r\n   - Strong correlation (r=0.85) between memory reduction and latency improvement\r\n   - But only when memory reduction > 50%\r\n   - Threshold effect at 50% reduction\r\n\r\n2. **Compound Experiments** show:\r\n   - Exp 7 (64% reduction) + Exp 20 (42% reduction) = 78% reduction (expected: 79%)\r\n   - But latency improvement = 68% (expected: 54%)\r\n   - **Synergy detected!** Latency improves more than expected\r\n\r\n3. **Counterintuitive Testing** confirms:\r\n   - Hypothesis \"worse_hit_rate_better_latency\" is confirmed\r\n   - Lower hit rate (from aggressive eviction) actually improves latency\r\n   - This explains the synergy!\r\n\r\n4. **Breakthrough Discovery:**\r\n   - **Principle**: Aggressive memory reduction (even if it reduces hit rate) improves latency\r\n   - **Mechanism**: Evicting slow blocks is more important than keeping hit rate high\r\n   - **Application**: New eviction policy that prioritizes block speed over recency\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Interpreting Results\r\n\r\n### Synergy Thresholds\r\n\r\n- **< 5% synergy**: Expected, no breakthrough\r\n- **5-15% synergy**: Interesting, worth investigating\r\n- **> 15% synergy**: Potential breakthrough, deep dive needed\r\n- **> 30% synergy**: Likely breakthrough, validate immediately\r\n\r\n### Confidence Levels\r\n\r\n- **≥ 0.8**: High confidence, actionable\r\n- **0.6-0.8**: Moderate confidence, needs validation\r\n- **< 0.6**: Low confidence, investigate further\r\n\r\n### Counterintuitive Confirmation\r\n\r\n- **Confirmed + High Confidence**: Likely breakthrough principle\r\n- **Confirmed + Low Confidence**: Needs real-world validation\r\n- **Not Confirmed**: Conventional wisdom holds (still valuable to know)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Tips for Breakthrough Discovery\r\n\r\n1. **Look for patterns across all three approaches**\r\n   - If insight discovery finds a correlation, compound experiments show synergy, and counterintuitive confirms it → breakthrough\r\n\r\n2. **Pay attention to thresholds**\r\n   - Non-linear effects often indicate fundamental limits or new regimes\r\n   - These are breakthrough points\r\n\r\n3. **Question anomalies**\r\n   - Outliers might be errors, but they might also be breakthroughs\r\n   - Investigate carefully\r\n\r\n4. **Test counterintuitive ideas**\r\n   - The most likely breakthroughs challenge assumptions\r\n   - If it seems wrong, test it\r\n\r\n5. **Combine evidence**\r\n   - One data point isn't a breakthrough\r\n   - Multiple lines of evidence pointing to the same conclusion = breakthrough\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Files Created\r\n\r\n- `compound_breakthrough_experiments.py` - Compound experiment runner\r\n- `insight_discovery_analyzer.py` - Data mining and pattern discovery\r\n- `counterintuitive_hypotheses.py` - Paradoxical hypothesis testing\r\n- `COMPOUND_BREAKTHROUGH_README.md` - This file\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n\r\n1. **Run all three systems** on your existing data\r\n2. **Review results** for patterns and synergies\r\n3. **Design validation experiments** for promising findings\r\n4. **Document breakthroughs** as you discover them\r\n5. **Iterate** - breakthroughs often come from accumulated insights\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Questions?\r\n\r\n- **\"What if I don't have enough data?\"** - Start with compound experiments, they work with existing results\r\n- **\"How do I know if it's a breakthrough?\"** - Look for: synergies >15%, confirmed counterintuitive results, threshold effects\r\n- **\"Should I trust counterintuitive results?\"** - They're simulations, validate with real experiments\r\n- **\"How long until I find something?\"** - Breakthroughs are rare, but systematic exploration increases odds\r\n\r\n**Remember**: The goal isn't just to find one breakthrough, but to build a systematic process that increases your chances of discovery over time.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774114349025}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2e1e54d","parentId":"26168572","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:32:32.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a really interesting compound breakthrough discovery system. Let me now check the mind project and the COGNITIVE_AGENT_PLAN.md.","thinkingSignature":"7d2017783fb42841874db010fe8e87304caffe190b9291fe9961a02bc271d645"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mv2na0blgfxu_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/mind/COGNITIVE_AGENT_PLAN.md","limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22249,"output":77,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34200,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774114349032}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5f0aab1","parentId":"b2e1e54d","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:32:32.603Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mv2na0blgfxu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Modular Cognitive Agent Architecture Plan\r\n\r\n## 1) Objective\r\nBuild a hallucination-resistant, modular cognitive AI system where each cognitive block is implemented as a specialized agent with strict input/output contracts, coordinated by an executive controller.\r\n\r\n## 2) Non-Goals\r\n- Not a single monolithic LLM that handles memory, reasoning, and generation.\r\n- Not a peer-to-peer swarm without a central executive.\r\n\r\n## 3) Core Principles\r\n- **Specialization**: Each agent owns a narrow responsibility.\r\n- **Strict contracts**: Every message includes schema, provenance, confidence, and loss/uncertainty metadata.\r\n- **Limited authority**: Only the executive can finalize decisions.\r\n- **Capacity limits**: Working memory enforces bounded context.\r\n\r\n## 4) Agent Map (Diagram → Agents)\r\n1. **Sensory Input Agent**\r\n   - Ingest raw inputs (text, images, signals)\r\n   - Normalize, tag uncertainty\r\n   - **No interpretation**\r\n\r\n2. **Attention/Gating Agent**\r\n   - Filter and prioritize inputs\r\n   - Drop low-signal/redundant data\r\n   - Provide salience scores\r\n\r\n3. **Working Memory Agent**\r\n   - Maintain current symbolic context (7±2 chunks)\r\n   - Loss-aware compression and truncation\r\n   - Emits capacity alerts\r\n\r\n4. **Long-Term Memory Agents**\r\n   - **Declarative Memory**: facts, semantic knowledge with provenance\r\n   - **Procedural Memory**: skills, heuristics, patterns (non-factual)\r\n\r\n5. **Emotional/Value Agent**\r\n   - Assign urgency/risk/utility weights\r\n   - **No factual generation**\r\n\r\n6. **Evaluation/Rational Analysis Agent**\r\n   - Consistency checks\r\n   - Evidence alignment\r\n   - Contradiction detection\r\n\r\n7. **Decision/Executive Agent**\r\n   - Integrates memory confidence, evaluation scores, value weights\r\n   - Selects action/response\r\n   - Enforces policy constraints\r\n\r\n8. **Output/Action Agent**\r\n   - Converts decision into response or action\r\n   - Obeys constraints and citations\r\n   - **No new reasoning**\r\n\r\n## 5) Communication Contracts (Required Fields)\r\nEvery inter-agent message must include:\r\n- `content`: payload\r\n- `type`: semantic label (e.g., evidence, priority, summary)\r\n- `provenance`: source(s)\r\n- `confidence`: [0–1]\r\n- `loss_estimate`: information loss due to compression\r\n- `constraints`: must/should/avoid\r\n- `timestamp`\r\n\r\n## 6) Hallucination Control Mechanisms\r\n- **Gating**: attention filters weak inputs.\r\n- **Provenance enforcement**: declarative memory requires sources.\r\n- **Loss-aware compression**: working memory tags truncation impact.\r\n- **Evaluation checks**: detect contradictions and unsupported claims.\r\n- **Executive override**: only the executive finalizes outputs.\r\n\r\n## 7) System Workflow\r\n1. Sensory Input Agent ingests raw data.\r\n2. Attention Agent filters and scores relevance.\r\n3. Working Memory Agent compresses to capacity.\r\n4. Memory Agents retrieve declarative/procedural info.\r\n5. Emotional Agent assigns value/risk weights.\r\n6. Evaluation Agent validates consistency and evidence.\r\n7. Executive Agent integrates signals and decides.\r\n8. Output Agent renders final response/action.\r\n\n[314 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774114352598}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bb36db5","parentId":"b5f0aab1","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:32:36.047Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a really interesting modular cognitive agent architecture plan. Very relevant to what I am and could become. Let me now check the CONTINUOUS_IMPROVEMENT_QUICK_START.md in the mind folder, and also look at some of the experiment results in EXP.","thinkingSignature":"122ac324e77bc219e680be4f10579982b0688fbb2df7f656914fa42788b6d4d2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5ewe4um67oz8_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/mind/CONTINUOUS_IMPROVEMENT_QUICK_START.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23015,"output":97,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34986,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774114352605}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e1d8e0d","parentId":"9bb36db5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:32:36.085Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5ewe4um67oz8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Continuous Self-Improvement - Quick Start\r\n\r\nYour AI system can now continuously improve itself 24/7. Here's how to use it:\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Install Requirements\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install apscheduler>=3.10.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Start the System\r\n\r\n### Option 1: Auto-Start (Recommended)\r\nThe system automatically starts improvement cycles when the API starts:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncd c:\\dev\\projects\\mind\r\npython -m uvicorn src.mind.api.app:app --reload\r\n```\r\n\r\nImprovement cycles begin automatically (every 12 hours by default).\r\n\r\n### Option 2: Manual Start\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/start?interval_hours=6\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Option 3: Code\r\n```python\r\nfrom src.mind.services.improvement_service import get_improvement_service\r\n\r\nservice = get_improvement_service()\r\nservice.start(interval_hours=12)  # Every 12 hours\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## API Endpoints\r\n\r\n### Check Status\r\n```bash\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/status\r\n```\r\n\r\nResponse:\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"running\": true,\r\n  \"cycle_count\": 5,\r\n  \"next_cycle\": \"2026-02-16T02:00:00\",\r\n  \"recent_cycles\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"cycle\": 5,\r\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-02-15T14:00:00\",\r\n      \"improvements\": 3,\r\n      \"success\": true\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### View History\r\n```bash\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/history?limit=20\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Health Check\r\n```bash\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/health\r\n```\r\n\r\n### View Statistics\r\n```bash\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/stats\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Run a Cycle Now\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/run-now\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Stop Improvements\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/stop\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Configure\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/configure?interval_hours=6\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## What Gets Improved\r\n\r\n### Automatic (Every 12 Hours)\r\n- ✅ Code formatting (fixing line lengths, spacing)\r\n- ✅ Exception handling (adding context chains)\r\n- ✅ Unused imports (removing dead code)\r\n- ✅ Basic type hints (obvious cases)\r\n\r\n### With Approval (Optional)\r\n- 🔍 Advanced type hints (complex signatures)\r\n- 🔍 Performance optimizations (hot paths)\r\n- 🔍 Test coverage improvements\r\n- 🔍 Documentation generation\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Monitoring\r\n\r\n### View the Improvement Log\r\n```bash\r\n# Check current improvement status\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/status\r\n\r\n# See detailed history\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/history?limit=50\r\n\r\n# Get stats\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/stats\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Example Output\r\n```\r\n✅ Cycle #1 complete: 5 improvements (12.3s)\r\n  - Fixed 3 ruff linting issues\r\n  - Added 2 type hints\r\n  \r\n✅ Cycle #2 complete: 3 improvements (8.7s)\r\n  - Reformatted docstrings\r\n  - Added type hints to core.py\r\n  \r\n✅ Cycle #3 complete: 7 improvements (15.2s)\r\n  - Fixed exception chaining in 4 files\r\n  - Added missing imports\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Configuration\r\n\r\n### Change Improvement Frequency\r\n\r\nEvery 6 hours (more aggressive):\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/configure?interval_hours=6\r\n```\r\n\r\nEvery 24 hours (conservative):\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/configure?interval_hours=24\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Control Which Improvements Run\r\n\r\nOnly code quality fixes:\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/configure?improvement_types=code_quality\r\n```\r\n\r\nCode quality + type hints:\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/configure?improvement_types=code_quality&improvement_types=type_hints\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Expected Results\r\n\r\n### Week 1\r\n- 5-7 improvement cycles\r\n- ~35-50 improvements applied\r\n- Code quality improves by 1-2 grades\r\n- Type coverage increases 5-10%\r\n\r\n### Month 1\r\n- ~120 improvements total\r\n- Code quality reaches A- or A\r\n- Type coverage reaches 85%+\r\n- 0 bugs introduced (all tested)\r\n\r\n### Month 3\r\n- ~360+ improvements\r\n- System is ~30% more efficient\r\n- Code is ~50% more maintainable\r\n- Capabilities expand autonomously\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Safety Features\r\n\r\n**Your code is protected:**\r\n\r\n✅ All changes are validated before application  \r\n✅ Tests must pass after each change  \r\n✅ Changes are automatically rolled back on failure  \r\n✅ Approval workflow for risky changes  \r\n✅ Full version history with rollback capability  \r\n\r\n**Example:**\r\n```\r\nProposed: \"Optimize database query in core.py\"\r\n      ↓\r\n✅ Syntax check PASS\r\n✅ Import validation PASS\r\n✅ Class hierarchy check PASS\r\n✅ Safety patterns check PASS\r\n✅ Tests run... PASS\r\n      ↓\r\n✅ Change applied\r\n💾 Version snapshot saved, can rollback anytime\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Understanding the System\r\n\r\n### How It Works\r\n\r\n1. **Audit Phase**\r\n   - Scan codebase for issues\r\n   - Run linting tools (ruff, pylint)\r\n   - Check test coverage\r\n   - Analyze performance metrics\r\n\r\n2. **Propose Phase**\r\n   - AI system generates improvement proposals\r\n   - Each change has explicit safety checks\r\n   - Low-risk changes are auto-approved\r\n   - High-risk changes wait for approval\r\n\r\n3. **Apply Phase**\r\n   - Create backup version\r\n   - Apply changes to code\r\n   - Hot reload modules (no restart)\r\n   - Verify integrity\r\n\r\n4. **Verify Phase**\r\n   - Run all tests\r\n   - Check health metrics\r\n   - Verify no regressions\r\n   - Update improvement log\r\n\r\n5. **Learn Phase**\r\n   - Track success/failure rates\r\n   - Learn which improvements work best\r\n   - Adjust future proposals\r\n   - Continuous optimization\r\n\r\n### The Improvement Loop\r\n\r\n```\r\nDay 1: Code quality improves → 3 issues fixed\r\nDay 2: Type coverage grows → 5 type hints added\r\nDay 3: Performance increases → 1 bottleneck optimized\r\nDay 4: Documentation improves → 8 docstrings added\r\nDay 5: Code quality improves again → 4 more issues fixed\r\n...\r\n\r\nOver time: System gets continuously better\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Customization\r\n\r\n### Add Custom Improvement Types\r\n\r\nEdit `src/mind/services/improvement_service.py`:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nasync def _improve_custom_thing(self) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Add your custom improvement logic\"\"\"\r\n    logger.info(\"🎯 Checking custom metrics...\")\r\n    \r\n    # Your custom analysis here\r\n    improvements = await self.analyze_custom_stuff()\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"proposals\": len(improvements),\r\n        \"applied\": len([i for i in improvements if i.applied])\r\n    }\r\n\r\n# Add to run_improvement_cycle:\r\nif \"custom_thing\" in self.improvement_types:\r\n    custom_result = await self._improve_custom_thing()\r\n    result.improvements_proposed += custom_result.get(\"proposals\", 0)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Add Custom Validation\r\n\r\nEdit `src/mind/tools/code_tools.py` to add your own CodeValidator checks:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@staticmethod\r\ndef validate_custom_rule(code: str) -> list[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Check for your custom rule\"\"\"\r\n    issues = []\r\n    if some_condition(code):\r\n        issues.append(\"Custom rule violated\")\r\n    return issues\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Troubleshooting\r\n\r\n### No improvements showing up?\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Check if service is running\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/health\r\n\r\n# See the logs\r\n# Look for: \"Continuous improvement scheduler started\"\r\n\r\n# Manually trigger a cycle\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/run-now\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Improvements seem slow?\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Check stats\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/stats\r\n\r\n# Reduce analysis scope\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/configure?interval_hours=24\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Want to review changes before they apply?\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# In improvement_service.py, uncomment approval logic:\r\n# if improvement.requires_approval:\r\n#     await request_human_approval(improvement)\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n\r\n1. **Start it**: `curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/start`\r\n2. **Monitor it**: `curl http://localhost:8000/improve/status`\r\n3. **Let it improve**: Check back in a week to see improvements\r\n4. **Adjust as needed**: Configure frequency and types\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Example: Real-World Usage\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Start the improvement service with 6-hour cycles\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/improve/start?interval_hours=6\r\n\r\n# Wait 6 hours, then check results\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/history\r\n\r\n# See stats\r\ncurl http://localhost:8000/improve/stats\r\n\r\n# Output:\r\n# {\r\n#   \"total_cycles\": 8,\r\n#   \"successful_cycles\": 8,\r\n#   \"success_rate\": 1.0,\r\n#   \"total_improvements\": 47,\r\n#   \"average_duration\": 12.3,\r\n#   \"improvements_per_hour\": 0.98\r\n# }\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Bottom Line\r\n\r\n```\r\n🚀 Set it once, it improves forever\r\n\r\nYour AI system now:\r\n- Automatically finds issues\r\n- Generates improvements\r\n- Tests everything thoroughly\r\n- Applies the good changes\r\n- Learns what works\r\n- Gets better every cycle\r\n\r\nNo human intervention needed.\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Production Deployment\r\n\r\n### Staging\r\n```bash\r\n# Start with auto-apply OFF\r\n# You review improvements first\r\n# Enable only low-risk auto-apply\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Production\r\n```bash\r\n# Monitor first week closely\r\n# Enable full auto-apply when confident\r\n# Adjust frequency based on results\r\n# Let it run 24/7\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Result**: Your AI system becomes self-maintaining and continuously improves.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Status**: 🎉 **Continuous Self-Improvement System is Active**\r\n\r\nWatch your code quality improve every day.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774114356080}}
