{"type":"message","id":"4c56c5e2","parentId":"33794e2c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:36:26.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n1. Make a plan to implement the features I want\n2. Help them start monetizing their projects\n\nLet me think about this. I should be strategic - I shouldn't just pick any project, I should focus on things that are actually buildable and monetizable. Let me think about each project and what the monetization angle could be.\n\nLet me first look at the projects I've found and assess them for:\n1. How viable they are to implement as features/tools\n2. How monetizable they are\n3. What's the path to revenue\n\nProjects I found:\n1. **EXP** - LLM inference optimization (CAAE) - has production-ready results, clear B2B use case\n2. **Mind** - Cognitive agent architecture - could be a developer tool or API\n\n\n3. **Temporal-Attention** - Memory system for AI agents - API/service potential\n4. **COG-research** - Research project - harder to monetize directly\n5. **Neu-project** - ML research - also research-heavy\n6. **Component-crate**, **shared-browser**, **infant**, **gpume**, **tta-crypto**, **werender**, **web_design**, **sep-w**, **rigman**, **time**, **novel**, **newage**, **selfhelper-main** - various projects I haven't explored yet\n\nI should dig into some of these unexplored projects to understand what they do and whether they have monetization potential, then come back with a structured plan that prioritizes the most viable revenue opportunities.\n\nLooking at what I've already seen - temporal-attention is solid for AI agent infrastructure, mind could become a developer tool or API, and EXP is clearly positioned as B2B SaaS with production validation. Let me scan the remaining projects to see if any of them are actually products or services rather than experiments.","thinkingSignature":"89d44bc139322419ce2f512c4a16740f3e4efa4aca2227453131fe54d25e1da7"},{"type":"text","text":"