{"type":"message","id":"17bd5218","parentId":"a590f110","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:36:51.412Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_94yvhec8bat4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Infant: Synthetic Human Cognitive Architecture\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/PyTorch-2.0+-ee4c2c?style=flat-square&logo=pytorch\" alt=\"PyTorch\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue?style=flat-square&logo=python\" alt=\"Python\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green?style=flat-square\" alt=\"License\">\n</p>\n\nA synthetic human cognitive architecture with persistent identity, memory, and learning. Built to explore continuous persistent temporal cognition.\n\n## 🎯 What is Infant?\n\nInfant is an AI system that:\n- **Remembers who it is** - Core identity persists across sessions\n- **Learns without forgetting** - Dual-head architecture protects what matters\n- **Dreams to consolidate** - Offline memory tier promotion\n- **Sets and pursues goals** - Active goal system\n- **Validates itself** - Self-consistency checking\n\n## 🧠 Architecture\n\n```\nInfant\n├── Dual-Head Architecture\n│   ├── Core Head (frozen) → identity, values, core memory\n│   └── Flexible Head → new learning\n│\n├── Memory System (4 tiers)\n│   ├── Working Memory (20 items)\n│   ├── Raw Experiences (500)\n│   ├── Patterns (100) \n│   ├── Knowledge (50)\n│   └── Wisdom (20)\n│\n├── Self-Model\n│   ├── Motor → Sensory predictor\n│   └── Self/Other classifier\n│\n├── Values System\n│   └── Core values with strengths\n│\n├── Goal System\n│   ├── Priority queue\n│   └── Progress tracking\n│\n└── Validation\n    └── Coherence checking\n```\n\n## 🔬 Experiments\n\n10 experiments proving the architecture works:\n\n| Experiment | Result |\n|------------|--------|\n| Mirror Test | ✓ Pass - Distinguishes self from external |\n| Continuity Test | ✓ Pass - Persistent state preserves knowledge |\n| Body Ownership | ✓ Pass - Sensorimotor = body ownership |\n| Value Formation | ✓ Pass - Preferences emerge from experience |\n| Value Stability | ✓ Pass - Values survive contradiction |\n| Untaught Value | ✓ Pass - Learns principles, not patterns |\n| Memory Persistence | ✓ Pass - Dual-head prevents forgetting |\n| Personality Coherence | ✓ Pass - Identity stable through updates |\n| Integration | ✓ Pass - New info integrates without destabilizing |\n| Fracture Prevention | ✓ Pass - Extreme stress doesn't break identity |\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n```python\nfrom infant.infant_complete import Infant\n\n# Create Infant\ninfant = Infant()\n\n# Form identity (once)\ninfant.form_identity(\"I am a curious, honest AI\")\n\n# Set values\ninfant.set_value(\"honesty\", 1.0)\ninfant.set_value(\"curiosity\", 0.9)\n\n# Freeze core (identity + values protected)\ninfant.freeze_core()\n\n# Learn new things (flexible, won't affect core)\ninfant.learn(\"The sky is blue\", importance=0.6)\n\n# Set goals\ninfant.set_goal(\"Understand consciousness\", priority=0.9)\n\n# Dream consolidation (offline)\ninfant.dream()\n\n# Validate\nstatus = infant.validate()\nprint(status)\n```\n\n## 📁 Project Structure\n\n```\ninfant/\n├── infant_complete.py      # Main Infant class\n├── cognitive_architecture.py # Dual-head implementation\n├── memory_enhanced.py      # Memory system + consolidation\n├── train_dualhead.py       # Training integration\n├── experiments/\n│   ├── mirror_test.py\n│   ├── value_formation_test.py\n│   ├── continuity_test.py\n│   ├── memory_persistence_test.py\n│   └── ...\n├── SYNTHETIC_HUMAN.md      # Full development plan\n├── DUAL_HEAD_ARCHITECTURE.md # Technical docs\n└── EXPERIMENTS.md         # Experiment results\n```\n\n## 🔑 Key Innovation: Dual-Head Architecture\n\nThe breakthrough: **catastrophic forgetting is a weight-sharing problem**.\n\nSolution: separate paths + freeze\n\n```python\nclass DualHeadBlock(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.encoder = ...\n        self.core_head = ...  # Protected, frozen after formation\n        self.flex_head = ...  # Flexible, always learning\n```\n\n- **Core head** (frozen): identity, values, core memories\n- **Flexible head**: new learning, opinions, skills\n\nThis mirrors human cognition: core values don't change, but we learn new things every day.\n\n## 📊 Benchmark Results\n\nCompared against EWC on continual learning:\n\n| Method | Accuracy | Forgetting |\n|--------|----------|-----------|\n| Baseline | 51.4% | -39.3pp |\n| EWC | 54.1% | -28.7pp |\n| **Dual-Head** | 84.7% | -14.5pp |\n\n**+33pp improvement** over baseline.\n\n## 🌐 Links\n\n- GitHub: https://github.com/toxzak-svg/infant\n- Moltbook: @clawhedgehog\n\n## 📝 Citation\n\n```bibtex\n@software{infant2026,\n  title = {Infant: Synthetic Human Cognitive Architecture},\n  author = {Zach Maronek},\n  year = {2026},\n  url = {https://github.com/toxzak-svg/infant}\n}\n```\n\n## 🤝 Contributing\n\nBuilt by Zach with help from Claw. Contributions welcome!\n\n## 📄 License\n\nMIT\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774114611408}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d311d5c","parentId":"17bd5218","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:36:54.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the component-crate spec and selfhelper-main README.","thinkingSignature":"d9770fe64fb9f2e42650acfe7eca0cb3cd2ff48c76e0b0b38ceaf6017166218f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wx5bfeh0e643_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/dev/component-crate/SPEC.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38373,"output":50,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50297,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774114611414}}
{"type":"message","id":"0802ef61","parentId":"6d311d5c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:36:54.549Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wx5bfeh0e643_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Component Crate - Specification\n\n## The Idea\n\nA VS Code extension for managing Tailwind + React components + optional GitHub import.\n\n**Core value:** \"I never have to hunt for that modal/table again.\"\n\n**The Hook:** Free users get 10 components saved. Pay for more.\n\n---\n\n## Core Features\n\n### Phase 1: VS Code Extension (Primary)\n\n1. **Inline Search** — Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+P to search your crate\n2. **Quick Insert** — Paste component at cursor\n3. **Save Selection** — Select code → save to crate\n4. **GitHub Import** — Import from connected repo (any file/folder)\n5. **Live Preview** — Hover to preview component\n6. **Limit System** — Free: 10 components, then pay\n\n### Phase 2: Web Companion\n\n- Full crate management (web dashboard)\n- Settings, billing, account\n- GitHub connection management (if not in VS Code)\n\n### Phase 3: Marketplace (v2)\n\n- After 1,000+ crates\n- Buy/sell component packs\n\n---\n\n## GitHub Integration\n\n- **Import from repo** — Pull any component/path from your GitHub repos\n- **Sync** — Keep components synced with your source of truth (optional)\n- **Partial imports** — Select specific files/folders from a repo\n- **Auth:** GitHub OAuth (user grants repo access)\n- **How it works:**\n  1. Connect GitHub account\n  2. Browse your repos in VS Code\n  3. Select folder/file → Import to crate\n  4. Optional: Mark as \"synced\" (pull updates later)\n\n---\n\n## The Limit (Freemium)\n\n| Tier | Components | Price |\n|------|-----------|-------|\n| Free | 10 | $0 |\n| Hobby | 50 | $5/mo |\n| Pro | 200 | $15/mo |\n| Team | Unlimited | $49/mo |\n\n- GitHub imports don't count against limit\n- Marketplace purchases don't count against limit\n\n---\n\n## User Flows\n\n### Onboarding (VS Code)\n1. Install extension from VS Code Marketplace\n2. (Optional) Connect GitHub for import\n3. Start saving components\n\n### Saving a Component\n1. Select code in editor → Right-click \"Save to Crate\"\n2. Add name, tags, choose folder\n3. Saved to local storage (or cloud if signed in)\n\n### GitHub Import\n1. Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+P → \"Import from GitHub\"\n2. Browse repos → Select file/folder\n3. Import to crate\n\n---\n\n## Technical Stack\n\n### VS Code Extension\n- **Framework:** TypeScript + VS Code API\n- **Build:** VSCE (VS Code Extension Manager)\n- **State:** Local JSON + optional cloud sync\n- **GitHub API:** Octokit for repo access\n- **Editor:** CodeMirror or Monaco (embedded for preview)\n\n### Web Companion (Optional)\n- **Frontend:** Next.js + React\n- **Styling:** Tailwind\n- **Auth:** GitHub OAuth\n- **Database:** PostgreSQL (Supabase/Neon)\n\n---\n\n## Deployment\n\n### Phase 1: VS Code Extension\n\n| Resource | Service | Est. Cost |\n|----------|---------|-----------|\n| VS Code Marketplace | Free | $0 |\n| Extension Hosting | GitHub Releases | $0 |\n\n### Phase 2: Web + Cloud Sync\n- Vercel (frontend)\n- Supabase/Neon (database)\n\n### Phase 3: Marketplace\n- Stripe Connect\n\n---\n\n## Why This Works\n\n1. **In-editor workflow** — Don't leave VS Code\n2. **GitHub import** — Pull from existing repos\n3. **Storage hook** — 10 free, then pay\n4. **No lock-in** — Your code, copy-pasteable\n\n---\n\n## Names (Pick One)\n\n- Component Crate (current)\n- Crate\n- Clip\n- DevComponents\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [ ] Initialize VS Code extension project\n- [ ] Basic extension setup (command palette, storage)\n- [ ] Search + insert functionality\n- [ ] GitHub OAuth + repo browser\n- [ ] Landing page for extension\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774114614545}}
