{"type":"message","id":"35fd772c","parentId":"d05011d6","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:48:44.895Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me set up the cron job for self-improvement. I'll check if there's a self-improvement script in the mind project or the selfhelper-main project that I can run.\n\nFor the self-improvement cron, I should:1. Periodically scan my workspace code for improvements\n2. Auto-fix issues\n\nBut actually, the self-improvement cron I want is more like: periodically run the self-improvement scripts from the selfhelper-main project and apply improvements to the workspace.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for me is to:\n1. Create a cron job that runs a script to review my own code (workspace files) and generate improvement suggestions\n2. Apply low-risk fixes automatically\n\n\n3. Flag the high-risk ones for review\n\nNow I need to set up the cron job. The most practical approach is to have it periodically analyze my workspace code using a script that audits and improves the workspace code, though I need to be careful about what changes get auto-applied versus flagged for review.\n\nActually, I think the better move is to first complete my memory and provenance implementation, then set up the cron job afterward.","thinkingSignature":"d53cb678acc90a085e39d418aa5ee6c3c1812238eeedf9c3c0352e09ecc52a1c"},{"type":"text","text":"Good. Now let me set up the self-improvement cron job and also add provenance tracking to my responses.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a9cy7p90qy94_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49346,"output":272,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61492,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774115316363}}
