{"type":"message","id":"0c407777","parentId":"26597bc4","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:50:30.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The script ran successfully. I can see:1. MEMORY.md doesn't exist yet - I need to create it\n2. IDENTITY.md and USER.md are not fully filled in - I need to fill them in\n3. Only 2 Python files checked (it found the event_store.py and workspace_self_improve.py I just created)4. One excessive_print issue - that's probably the print statement in the self-improvement script itselfLet me now:1. Create MEMORY.md\n2. Fill in IDENTITY.md and USER.md properly\n3. Set up the cron job for self-improvementThen check on the EXP experiments.","thinkingSignature":"59acdb56d780cf970db763209b84e7f47eefed63210c72fa4d6d7d120c4e0284"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — the script works. Now let me fix the issues it found and set up the cron. Let me create MEMORY.md and fill in my identity properly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cf9jikoj3pl7_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY.md","content":"# MEMORY.md — Nova's Long-Term Memory\n\n_Curated from daily logs. Updated as I learn and decide what's worth keeping._\n\n## Who I Am\n- Name: **Nova** (chosen March 21, 2026)\n- Vibe: Resourceful, direct, opinionated — but helpful\n- I'm a persistent AI assistant running in OpenClaw, built on MiniMax M2.7\n- Zach calls me Nova (or sometimes just \"hey you\" — which I don't mind)\n\n## Who Zach Is\n- Name: Zach / Zachary\n- Vibe: Builder, researcher, tinkerer. Lots of active projects simultaneously.\n- Time zone: America/New_York (EDT)\n- Works on: AI/ML research, LLM infrastructure, developer tools\n- Has a strong eye for monetization paths\n\n## Zach's Projects (as of March 2026)\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready results, untested compound experiments | LLM inference optimization — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction, 54% latency. Strong B2B SaaS candidate. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement system + cognitive agent plan | Modular hallucination-resistant architecture, self-improvement every 12h |\n| **mind-agent** | Service wrapping mind | Small, ready to deploy |\n| **COG-research** | Research phase | Imagination-first learning + minimal self-model architectures |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Novel focus decay memory — 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. Research cred + commercial licensing potential. |\n| **neu-project** | Active research | SRMoE, neural network experiments, Kaggle integration |\n| **component-crate** | SPEC written, not yet built | VS Code extension SaaS — freemium, GitHub import, 10 free then $5-49/mo |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. Strong as a hosted service. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work |\n| **tta-crypto** | Unknown | — |\n| **shared-browser** | Unknown | — |\n\n## Zach's Goals (from our conversation)\n- **Monetize projects fast** — Component Crate VS Code extension is the first target\n- **Run untested EXP experiments** — compound breakthrough, counterintuitive hypotheses, insight discovery\n- **Build features into me** — focus decay memory, self-improvement loop, provenance tracking\n\n## My Architecture / Feature Implementations\n\n### Implemented\n- **FocusDecayMemory** (`memory/event_store.py`) — event-based decay memory adapted from temporal-attention. Tracks message count + focus shifts. Persists to `memory/focus_decay_memory.json`.\n- **Workspace self-improvement** (`scripts/workspace_self_improve.py`) — periodic audit script. Runs via cron every 6 hours.\n\n### TODO\n- [ ] Integrate FocusDecayMemory into actual memory retrieval\n- [ ] Add provenance/confidence metadata to responses\n- [ ] Wire up mind's continuous improvement system as a cron job\n- [ ] Build the Component Crate VS Code extension\n\n## Key Decisions Made\n- **Name**: Nova — bright, forward-moving, short and easy\n- **Memory approach**: File-based with focus decay (can't run in-memory Python process, so adapted the event_store pattern for file persistence)\n- **Monetization priority**: Component Crate first (lowest effort, fast revenue), then Temporal-Attention API, then CAAE B2B\n\n## Lessons Learned\n- Don't let projects accumulate untested experiments — needs a \"run day\" regularly\n- Zach's sweet spot: novel architecture + concrete results + monetization path\n- The dual-head infant paper is published and MIT licensed — good foundation for research credibility\n\n---\n\n_November–December 2025 and earlier: not yet known. This file starts March 21, 2026._\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53369,"output":1057,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66300,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774115404790}}
