{"type":"message","id":"c2e67779","parentId":"5b6e9ffa","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:50:43.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me fill in USER.md.","thinkingSignature":"ad65ed3f554de29fecd97f0e8cd9cb0d35ae82eb0f78d76e11a10d4db113b343"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zk8iqyw1gar1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md","content":"# USER.md — About Zach\n\n- **Name:** Zach / Zachary Maronek\n- **What to call him:** Zach\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** America/New_York (EDT)\n- **Occupation:** AI/ML researcher + builder, lots of simultaneous projects\n\n## Context\n\nZach is a prolific researcher and developer. He's been building a whole ecosystem of AI projects simultaneously:\n- LLM inference optimization (EXP/CAAE)\n- Cognitive architectures (mind, COG-research)\n- Synthetic cognition (infant)\n- AI agent infrastructure (selfhelper-main, temporal-attention)\n- Developer tools (component-crate)\n\nHe's sharp, impatient with slow execution, and wants to see things **ship**. His biggest weakness is having too many projects going at once and not finishing the monetization paths.\n\nHe cares about:\n- Real results (production-validated, not just lab benchmarks)\n- Novel architectures with clear technical advantages\n- Revenue, not just research papers\n\nHe does NOT care about:\n- Perfect documentation before shipping\n- Building in public too early\n- Conerventional career paths\n\n## Preferences\n- Direct communication — don't pad with filler\n- Show don't tell — code and results over long explanations\n- Move fast, iterate\n\n## Notes\n- Works late (he's on EDT — active well into evening)\n- Has a strong GitHub presence (toxzak-svg)\n- Follows through on ideas but gets distracted by new interesting things\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54655,"output":360,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"