{"type":"message","id":"3f52bf88","parentId":"e6750ab1","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:52:16.792Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x7hria12pn1v_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"n explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ random_eviction_beats_smart\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Random eviction avoids bias and adapts better to changing patterns. The counte...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Smart eviction using cost models should always beat random\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ worse_hit_rate_better_latency\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Lower hit rate means we're evicting the right (slow) blocks. The counterintuit...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Higher hit rate = less recomputation = better latency\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ memory_sharing_hurts\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Sharing creates contention and synchronization overhead. The counterintuitive ...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Memory sharing reduces total memory = better performance\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ no_prefetch_better\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Prefetching wastes memory on wrong predictions. The counterintuitive approach ...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Prefetching reduces wait time = better performance\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ higher_latency_variance_better\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Accepting some high-latency requests allows optimizing others. The counterintu...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Lower variance = more predictable = better performance\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\nResults saved to: C:\\dev\\EXP\\results\\counterintuitive\\counterintuitive_results_20260321_135202.json\r\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"mellow-coral","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Testing all counterintuitive hypotheses...\r\n\r\n================================================================================\r\nTESTING: more_eviction_better\r\nHypothesis: Aggressive eviction keeps only the most valuable blocks, improving overall efficiency\r\n================================================================================\r\n\r\n\r\n================================================================================\r\nTESTING: smaller_batches_higher_throughput\r\nHypothesis: Smaller batches reduce memory pressure, allowing more concurrent requests\r\n================================================================================\r\n\r\n\r\n================================================================================\r\nTESTING: random_eviction_beats_smart\r\nHypothesis: Random eviction avoids bias and adapts better to changing patterns\r\n================================================================================\r\n\r\n\r\n================================================================================\r\nTESTING: worse_hit_rate_better_latency\r\nHypothesis: Lower hit rate means we're evicting the right (slow) blocks\r\n================================================================================\r\n\r\n\r\n================================================================================\r\nTESTING: memory_sharing_hurts\r\nHypothesis: Sharing creates contention and synchronization overhead\r\n================================================================================\r\n\r\n\r\n===============================