gy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ worse_hit_rate_better_latency\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Lower hit rate means we're evicting the right (slow) blocks. The counterintuit...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Higher hit rate = less recomputation = better latency\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ memory_sharing_hurts\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Sharing creates contention and synchronization overhead. The counterintuitive ...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Memory sharing reduces total memory = better performance\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ no_prefetch_better\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Prefetching wastes memory on wrong predictions. The counterintuitive approach ...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Prefetching reduces wait time = better performance\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\n  ✓ higher_latency_variance_better\r\n    Confidence: 0.90\r\n    Explanation: Hypothesis CONFIRMED: Accepting some high-latency requests allows optimizing others. The counterintu...\r\n    Implications:\r\n      • This challenges the assumption that Lower variance = more predictable = better performance\r\n      • This may indicate a new optimization strategy that hasn't been explored\r\n\r\nResults saved to: C:\\dev\\EXP\\results\\counterintuitive\\counterintuitive_results_20260321_135202.json\r\n","name":"cd C:/dev/EXP"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774115536790}}
