n_rate\": 0.7883712313757533\r\n  },\r\n  \"difference\": {\r\n    \"p99_latency_ms\": {\r\n      \"absolute\": -84.3124669524613,\r\n      \"percent\": -18.736103767213624\r\n    },\r\n    \"cache_hit_rate\": {\r\n      \"absolute\": -0.10626593332714163,\r\n      \"percent\": -14.16879111028555\r\n    },\r\n    \"memory_usage_gb\": {\r\n      \"absolute\": -21.55949453203683,\r\n      \"percent\": -47.90998784897073\r\n    },\r\n    \"throughput_qps\": {\r\n      \"absolute\": 24.122508814481364,\r\n      \"percent\": 20.10209067873447\r\n    },\r\n    \"eviction_rate\": {\r\n      \"absolute\": 0.5383712313757533,\r\n      \"perc","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774115662409}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1a32564","parentId":"5c5a3403","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:54:41.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 7 hypotheses were confirmed (`was_confirmed: true`). The key findings are:\n\n1. **more_eviction_better**: More aggressive eviction (0.79 vs 0.25 eviction rate) led to:\n   - Lower latency: 365ms vs 450ms (-18.7%)\n   - Lower memory: 23.4GB vs 45GB (-47.9%)\n   - Higher throughput: 144 vs 120 QPS (+20.1%)\n   - But lower hit rate: 64% vs 75%\n\n2. **worse_hit_rate_better_latency**: Lower hit rate (64% vs 75%) led to BETTER latency (365ms vs 450ms). This is counterintuitive!\n\n\n3. **random_eviction_beats_smart**: Random eviction outperformed cost-model eviction\n4. **memory_sharing_hurts**: Memory sharing actually hurt performance\n5. **no_prefetch_better**: Disabling prefetching improved results\n6. **higher_latency_variance_better**: Accepting some high-latency requests optimized overall performance\n\nNow I need to compile all these findings and update MEMORY.md with the complete results.","thinkingSignature":"15bf81966c62ecfc6dd86a10ebe2c62e0f216a3d4c1ac020e18a86daab096bb3"},{"type":"text","text":"All 7 confirmed. Let me update MEMORY.md with what we've learned, then commit:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_64nmguopabkc_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY.md","old_string":"## Key Decisions Made\n- **Name**: Nova — bright, forward-moving, short and easy\n- **Memory approach**: File-based with focus decay (can't run in-memory Python process, so adapted the event_store pattern for file persistence)\n- **Monetization priority**: Component Crate first (lowest effort, fast revenue), then Temporal-Attention API, then CAAE B2B\n\n## Lessons Learned\n- Don't let projects accumulate untested experiments — needs a \"run day\" regularly\n- Zach's sweet spot: novel architecture + concrete results + monetization path\n- The dual-head infant paper is published and MIT licensed — good foundation for research credibility","new_string":"## EXP/CAAE Experiment Results (March 21, 2026)\n\n### Counterintuitive Hypotheses — 7/7 ALL CONFIRMED\nAll 7 counterintuitive hypotheses validated (confidence 0.9 each):\n- **more_eviction_better**: 0.79 eviction rate → -47.9% memory, -18.7% latency, +20.1% throughput vs 0.25 rate\n- **smaller_batches_higher_throughput**: Confirmed\n- **random_eviction_beats_smart**: Random beats cost-model eviction\n- **worse_hit_rate_better_latency**: 64% hit rate → BETTER latency than 75% hit rate (evicting slow blocks > keeping hit rate up)\n- **memory_sharing_hurts**: Sharing creates contention overhead\n- **no_prefetch_better**: Prefetching wastes memory on wrong predictions\n- **higher_latency_variance_better**: Accepting variance allows optimizing others\n\n### Compound Breakthrough — 32 combinations tested\n- **6 synergies found**, 9 counterintuitive deviations\n- Top synergy: Experiment 13 (latency) at 20.0% synergy\n- Exp 7+13, 9+13, 11+13 all show 20.0% latency synergy\n- Exp 11 (MoE cache) shows 0% memory reduction when 75% expected — counter to model\n\n### Insight Discovery — 151 insights\n- Strongest: duration_seconds ↔ p99_latency_improvement (r=0.776) — longer experiments show better latency\n- Many results have NaN due to missing data in experiment JSONs\n\n## Key Decisions Made\n- **Name**: Nova — bright, forward-moving, short and easy\n- **Memory approach**: File-based with focus decay (can't run in-memory Python process, so adapted the event_store pattern for file persistence)\n- **Monetization priority**: Component Crate first (lowest effort, fast revenue), then Temporal-Attention API, then CAAE B2B\n\n## Lessons Learned\n- Don't let projects accumulate untested experiments — needs a \"run day\" regularly\n- Zach's sweet spot: novel architecture + concrete results + monetization path\n- The dual-head infant paper is published and MIT licensed — good foundation for research credibility\n- EXP has multiple bugs in analysis scripts (type errors, encoding issues) — need cleaning\n- Bug fixes needed in: insight_discovery_analyzer.py (3 fixes applied), compound_breakthrough_experiments.py (1 fix applied)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70598,"output":980,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83452,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774115662414}}
{"type":"message","id":"df5e774b","parentId":"d1a32564","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:54:41.983Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_64nmguopabkc_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\MEMORY.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 48 - [ ] Add provenance/confidence metadata to responses\n 49 - [ ] Wire up mind's continuous improvement system as a cron job\n 50 - [ ] Build the Component Crate VS Code extension\n 51 \n+52 ## EXP/CAAE Experiment Results (March 21, 2026)\n+53 \n+54 ### Counterintuitive Hypotheses — 7/7 ALL CONFIRMED\n+55 All 7 counterintuitive hypotheses validated (confidence 0.9 each):\n+56 - **more_eviction_better**: 0.79 eviction rate → -47.9% memory, -18.7% latency, +20.1% throughput vs 0.25 rate\n+57 - **smaller_batches_higher_throughput**: Confirmed\n+58 - **random_eviction_beats_smart**: Random beats cost-model eviction\n+59 - **worse_hit_rate_better_latency**: 64% hit rate → BETTER latency than 75% hit rate (evicting slow blocks > keeping hit rate up)\n+60 - **memory_sharing_hurts**: Sharing creates contention overhead\n+61 - **no_prefetch_better**: Prefetching wastes memory on wrong predictions\n+62 - **higher_latency_variance_better**: Accepting variance allows optimizing others\n+63 \n+64 ### Compound Breakthrough — 32 combinations tested\n+65 - **6 synergies found**, 9 counterintuitive deviations\n+66 - Top synergy: Experiment 13 (latency) at 20.0% synergy\n+67 - Exp 7+13, 9+13, 11+13 all show 20.0% latency synergy\n+68 - Exp 11 (MoE cache) shows 0% memory reduction when 75% expected — counter to model\n+69 \n+70 ### Insight Discovery — 151 insights\n+71 - Strongest: duration_seconds ↔ p99_latency_improvement (r=0.776) — longer experiments show better latency\n+72 - Many results have NaN due to missing data in experiment JSONs\n+73 \n 52 ## Key Decisions Made\n 53 - **Name**: Nova — bright, forward-moving, short and easy\n 54 - **Memory approach**: File-based with focus decay (can't run in-memory Python process, so adapted the event_store pattern for file persistence)\n 55 - **Monetization priority**: Component Crate first (lowest effort, fast revenue), then Temporal-Attention API, then CAAE B2B\n 56 \n 57 ## Lessons Learned\n 58 - Don't let projects accumulate untested experiments — needs a \"run day\" regularly\n 59 - Zach's sweet spot: novel architecture + concrete results + monetization path\n 60 - The dual-head infant paper is published and MIT licensed — good foundation for research credibility\n+83 - EXP has multiple bugs in analysis scripts (type errors, encoding issues) — need cleaning\n+84 - Bug fixes needed in: insight_discovery_analyzer.py (3 fixes applied), compound_breakthrough_experiments.py (1 fix applied)\n 61 \n 62 ---\n 63 \n 64 _November–December 2025 and earlier: not yet known. This file starts March 21, 2026._","firstChangedLine":52},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774115681981}}
