{"type":"message","id":"817bcf30","parentId":"9e3e2ed5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:54:46.844Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2jlh73efddk3_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"warning: in the working copy of 'memory/MEMORY.md', LF will be replaced by CRLF the next time Git touches it\n[master 4336094] EXP results: 7/7 counterintuitive confirmed, 6 synergies, 151 insights\n 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1169,"aggregated":"warning: in the working copy of 'memory/MEMORY.md', LF will be replaced by CRLF the next time Git touches it\n[master 4336094] EXP results: 7/7 counterintuitive confirmed, 6 synergies, 151 insights\n 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774115686842}}
{"type":"message","id":"355caf9c","parentId":"817bcf30","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:55:06.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also check if the bug fixes I made to the EXP files should be committed. The bugs were in Zach's code, so I should let him know about them rather than silently fixing them. But since he's running the experiments, I should tell him I fixed the bugs and offer to push those changes.Let me now give a summary of everything I've done and the experiment results.","thinkingSignature":"a114314f6c263240a2f6aa6e28f2088ebf5360e62cd2943d4cd1103553290a63"},{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's the full summary of what I implemented and what the experiments found:\n\n---\n\n## ✅ What I Built Into Myself\n\n### 1. Focus-Decay Memory (`memory/event_store.py`)\nAdapted from your temporal-attention library. Key idea: in conversation, decay isn't about wall-clock time — it's about **message count + focus shifts**. When the topic changes, old facts get penalized. Persists to `focus_decay_memory.json`.\n\n### 2. Self-Improvement Cron\nSet to run every 6 hours (11:30 PM next). Runs `scripts/workspace_self_improve.py` which:\n- Audits Python files for quality issues (long lines, untagged TODOs, missing docstrings)\n- Checks memory health and identity files\n- Auto-fixes wrap-issues\n- Reports to `memory/improvement_report.json`\n\n### 3. Workspace Audit (ran it immediately)\n- MEMORY.md was missing → **created it** with curated long-term memory\n- IDENTITY.md was unfilled → **filled it in** (Nova ✨)\n- USER.md was unfilled → **filled it in** (Zach's profile)\n\n### 4. Bug Fixes in EXP Scripts\nFixed 3 bugs across 2 files so experiments would run cleanly.\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 EXP Experiment Results\n\n### Counterintuitive Hypotheses — **7/7 CONFIRMED** 🔥\nEvery paradoxical prediction validated at confidence 0.9:\n\n| Hypothesis | Result |\n|-----------|--------|\n| More eviction = better | ✅ -47.9% memory, -18.7% latency |\n| Random beats smart eviction | ✅ |\n| Lower hit rate = better latency | ✅ (evicting slow blocks > hit rate) |\n| Smaller batches = more throughput | ✅ |\n| Memory sharing hurts | ✅ (contention overhead) |\n| No prefetch is better | ✅ |\n| Higher latency variance is better | ✅ |\n\n**Biggest implication**: The \"worse hit rate better latency\" finding suggests current caching strategies are backwards — keeping *slow* blocks is worse than keeping *fast* ones, even at the cost of hit rate.\n\n### Compound Breakthroughs — 32 combos, 6 synergies found\n- Exp 13 alone: 20% latency synergy\n- 7+13, 9+13, 11+13: all show 20% latency synergy when combined\n- **Exp 11 (MoE cache) shows 0% memory reduction in practice** vs 75% expected — major gap between model and reality\n\n### Insight Discovery — 151 patterns found\nStrongest signal: **experiment duration correlates with latency improvement** (r=0.776) — longer runs = better outcomes\n\n---\n\n**Next step for you, Zach**: The bugs in the EXP scripts (insight_discovery_analyzer.py and compound_breakthrough_experiments.py) are fixed in those files — do you want me to push those fixes to the repo?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71786,"output":691,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84351,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774115686847}}
