{"type":"message","id":"81f8049b","parentId":"d5e54a32","timestamp":"2026-03-21T18:22:06.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The recall returned empty. The issue is the search uses `threshold=0.01` which may be too high, or the `search` function doesn't match well. Let me check and fix the recall. The problem might be that the `search` function in FocusDecayMemory looks at fact values, but my key-based `focus.get(k)` for scored facts isn't matching the search correctly.\n\nActually, looking at the recall function:\n```python\nfocus_results = self.focus.search(query, threshold=0.01)\nlayer1 = [(self.focus.get(k).fact.value if self.focus.get(k) else None,\n           self.focus.get(k).combined_score if self.focus.get(k) else 0,\n           \"focus_decay\")\n          for k, _ in focus_results[:top_k]]\n```\n\nThe search returns keys with scores, and then I call get(key) to get the ScoredFact. But if the query doesn't match any value, search returns nothing. The query was \"what does Zach prefer\" but the stored values were \"Zach prefers direct communication...\" and \"Component Crate is the priority...\" — these are semantic matches, not substring matches. I need to either lower the threshold, improve the search to handle partial matches better, or rely more heavily on MEMORY.md which already contains \"Zach\" as a substring match.\n\nLet me test the search with a more targeted query to see if it's working at all.","thinkingSignature":"5dd8c3048b3a4e6b43615b381ad775fec5a8f8ffc39d5e3760d5f8b4bb9de86b"},{"type":"text","text":"The recall returned empty because `search()` does substring matching and \"Zach prefers\" ≠ \"what does Zach prefer\". Let me test and fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1b52gw42b6gv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace')\nfrom memory.manager import MemoryManager\nmm = MemoryManager()\n# Test with exact-ish match\nresult = mm.recall('Zach prefers')\nprint('Search for direct:', result)\nresult2 = mm.recall('Component Crate')\nprint('Search for Component:', result2)\nresult3 = mm.recall('project')\nprint('Search for project:', result3)\n\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81960,"output":457,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94291,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774117314165}}
{"type":"message","id":"885ee991","parentId":"81f8049b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T18:22:07.599Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1b52gw42b6gv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Traceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"<string>\", line 11, in <module>\r\n    result3 = mm.recall('project')\r\n  File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\manager.py\", line 99, in recall\r\n    if content and content not in seen:\r\n                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\nTypeError: cannot use 'list' as a set element (unhashable type: 'list')\r\nSearch for direct: [('[comm_style] Zach prefers direct communication over verbose padding', 0.5, 'notes:2026-03-21.md'), ('Zach prefers direct communication over verbose padding', 0.48902104070552854, 'focus_decay')]\r\nSearch for Component: [('Component Crate is the priority monetization project', 1.00069314718056, 'focus_decay'), ('**Monetize projects fast** � Component Crate VS Code extension is the first target', 0.6, 'MEMORY.md'), ('[ ] Build the Component Crate VS Code extension', 0.6, 'MEMORY.md'), ('**Monetization priority**: Component Crate first (lowest effort, fast revenue), then Temporal-Attention API, then CAAE B2B', 0.6, 'MEMORY.md'), ('[priority_project] Component Crate is the priority monetization project', 0.5, 'notes:2026-03-21.md')]\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":1209,"aggregated":"Traceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"<string>\", line 11, in <module>\r\n    result3 = mm.recall('project')\r\n  File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\manager.py\", line 99, in recall\r\n    if content and content not in seen:\r\n                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\nTypeError: cannot use 'list' as a set element (unhashable type: 'list')\r\nSearch for direct: [('[comm_style] Zach prefers direct communication over verbose padding', 0.5, 'notes:2026-03-21.md'), ('Zach prefers direct communication