{"type":"message","id":"576dbd6e","parentId":"362ddcb3","timestamp":"2026-03-21T18:24:21.964Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me build the VS Code extension myself. I'll scaffold it manually with the necessary files.\n\nFor a VS Code extension, I need:\n1. `package.json` - extension manifest\n2. `src/extension.ts` - main entry point\n3. `src/commands/search.ts` - search command\n4. `src/commands/save.ts` - save command\n5. `src/commands/insert.ts` - insert command\n6. `src/storage/store.ts` - local storage\n7. `src/github/api.ts` - GitHub integration\n8. `src/webview/preview.ts` - preview panel\n\n\n9. A `vsc-extension-quickstart.md` file for the project structure\n\nI'll set up a minimal scaffold with a command palette for searching components, right-click context menu for saving selected code, a webview panel for previews, GitHub OAuth using a PAT for authentication, and local JSON file storage with a freemium limit of 10 components before prompting users to upgrade.\n\nLet me start building this out.","thinkingSignature":"9264302e82e57090d7c8478ef780d76f9d9eaf8bbd47f1f87fea5dc56ea9f58c"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll build the VS Code extension myself. Let me scaffold it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ga24lua4yaen_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls C:/dev/component-crate","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83301,"output":271,"cacheRead":11874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95446,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774117454503}}
